$ corporate finance

Areas:
  • funding sources
  • capital structure of organizations/corporations
  • increase a firm's value for shareholders
  • allocating financial resources (toos and analysis)
  • balancing → science/finance/corporate/risk-management[risk] and profitability
  • maximizing entity's assets, cash flow and value of its stock

Three primary areas of capital resource allocation
  • capital budgeting
  • sources of capital
  • dividend policy

{ Capital structure

  The *capital structure* is a company's mix of financing methods it uses to raise funds.

  Methods:
    • dept financing: loans, bonds
    • equity financing: stocks

}

